{"lemma":"عَدُّ","slug":"عَدُّ","root":"ع.د.د","root_slug":"ع-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَدّ","root":"عدد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n28283","n28284"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8F%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to count"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to consider","tags":["ditransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"وَقَالُوا مَا لَنَا لَا نَرَىٰ رِجَالًا كُنَّا نَعُدُّهُم مِّنَ الْأَشْرَارِ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَدَّ (ʕadda) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"counting, calculation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"number"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕad.da/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28283","headword_ar":"عُدٌّ","root":"Ed","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eud~apN","text_ar":"عُدَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pustules in the face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IJ, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pustules that come forth in the faces of beautiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly, persons:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) pl. of the former [and app. of the latter also, which is probably a n. un.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEodaAdN","text_ar":"اَعْدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Marg. note in a copy of the S.)"}],"source_refs":["IJ","TA","O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n28284","headword_ar":"عِدٌّ","root":"Ed","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Multitude, muchness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,) in a thing. (K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahumo la*awuw Eid~K","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُمْ لَذَوُو عِدٍّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqibSK","text_ar":"وَقِبصٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in one of my copies of the S and in the O"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"la*uw","text_ar":"لَذُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in the other of my copies of the S and in the O"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiboDK","text_ar":"قِبْضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily they are many,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"numerous"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b2-  [It is also an epithet, signifying] Water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a continual increase;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that does not cease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the water of a spring; (S, O, Msb, K;) and of a well: (S, O, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"copious"},{"kind":"text","text":"water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spring"},{"kind":"text","text":"-water; rain-water being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karaEN","text_ar":"كَرَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"old"},{"kind":"text","text":"water,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that does not become exhausted:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, TA:) or an"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"old"},{"kind":"text","text":"well; (M, O, K;) said in the M [and O] to be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasabN","text_ar":"حَسَبٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eid~N","text_ar":"عِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA: [but see this in what follows:]) or in the dial. of Temeem,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much"},{"kind":"text","text":"water; but in the dial. of Bekr Ibn-Wáïl,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"little"},{"kind":"text","text":"water: (AO, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well"},{"kind":"text","text":"-water,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether little or much;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so accord. to a woman of Kiláb; opposed to that of the rain: accord. to Lth,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place which men make,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepare, wherein much water collects;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but Az says that this is a mistake: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEodaAdN","text_ar":"اَعْدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, A, O.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasabN Eid~N","text_ar":"حَسَبٌ عِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Old nobility"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, O:) accord. to IDrd, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eid~N","text_ar":"عِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to old water that does not become exhausted. (TA. [This derivation is probably correct: but see above.])       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadiydN","text_ar":"عَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  And see the paragraph here following."}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","Msb","TA","IDrd","AO","M","A"]}]}}